key2: whether the stats are derived from analysis of the "full" dataset (all pixels manually classified in polygons, including those that were not randomly selected for the training or validation sets - unequal sample sizes for each class) or only the 1/3 of the training data that was specifically withheld for validation ("validationOnly")
the class that was assigned by the classifier.
overall accuracy. One value for each data subset.
producer's accuracy: correct/total by column. Given a feature type, how often is that feature identified correctly? The complement of omission error. One value for each data subset.
consumer's accuracy: correct/total by row. Given a location, how often is that location correctly identified? The complement of the commission error. One value for each data subset.
How well did you do compared to a random classification? 0 = random, 1 = perfect.
these values are copied and pasted from the output of the earth engine script "supervised_classification/superdove/accuracy_check"
